Rude staff, poor customer service and worst food!! We ordered 2 Veg Fried Rice and 4 spring rolls.. The lady at the counter put 2 spring rolls in the box and closed it, I said we asked for 4, she then said only two were left which she didn’t say at the time of ordering.. then when it came to the rice, she filled rice for half the box on the one with spring rolls and filled double the quantity in the other.. when we asked for hot sauce which wasn’t there on the counter, she passed rude comments and brought one from under the table!  Now, the food part: it was almost closing time but the fried rice in their box was full and untouched and seemed like we were the only one that ordered.. I don’t know if they will save it for the next day!! The rice was terribly undercooked and we could bite the raw rice! Spring rolls were rubbery and salty. Literally the rudest staff I have ever encountered. I don’t like to leave bad reviews, but I was appalled by the staffs lack of customer service. Upon checking out, I asked the woman at the register for a soda.  She took my card and before she ran it, I asked if the soda was for large to which she replied “you didn’t tell me”  then she proceeded to swipe my credit card. I told her she should’ve asked me and then she told me that “ it wasn’t her job” and that I was responsible for telling her what size I wanted. I don’t know her name, but she was African American  wearing a blonde wig pulled into a low bun on her head. While I waited for my soda, she continued to make rude comments under her breath. I will never come here ever again. Food was okay but not worth the attitude.
